translations.The algorithm type \"%s\" is not a valid: The algorithm type "%s" is not a valid or supported algorithm type.
Creating a hash checksum of a file.
translations.Allows users to create a hash checksum o:
Allows users to create a hash checksum of a file.
        Possible algorithms are md5, sha1, sha256, sha384, sha512, sha3-256, sha3-512 and crc32.

        Just open the details view of the file (Sidebar). There should be a new tab called "Checksum".
        Select a algorithm and it will try to generate a hash.
        If you want an other algorithm, just click on the reload button.
Start byte must be a valid number.
End byte must be a valid number.
Start byte must be less than end byte.
Start byte must be 0 or greater.
End byte must be 0 or greater.
